'''Raymond D'Mello''' was a 20th-century Roman Catholic bishop in India.<ref>[http://www.catholic-hierarchy.org/bishop/bdmellor.html Catholic Hierarchy]</ref>

He was born in [[Aikala]]. D'Mello was [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Mangalore|Bishop of Mangalore]]<ref>[http://www.dioceseofmangalore.com/bishop/878-lists-of-bishops/15-bishops-from-the-diocese Diocesan web-site]</ref> from 1959 to 1964; and [[Roman Catholic Diocese of Allahabad|Bishop of Allahabad]]<ref>[http://dioceseofallahabad.org/Parishes/ST-PAUL-CHURCH-SULTANPUR.aspx# St Paul, Sultanpur]</ref> from 1964 to 1969. He was appointed Titular Bishop of Glenndálocha<ref>[http://www.gcatholic.org/dioceses/former/t0889.htm#32778 G Catholic]</ref> on 20 December 1969; and died on 24 November 1971.

